The paper deals with the design of algorithms for autonomous swarms of mobile robots, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of multiple sub-fields in computer science. The most relevant sub-category is likely to be cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), which focuses on the study of systems composed of multiple interacting agents. The paper also deals with the problem of gathering robots, which is a classic problem in robotics and falls under the scope of cs.RO (Robotics). The use of formal methods and reachability games suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the focus on self-organization and cooperation among robots suggests a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
